  "prompt": "What do you think the cutoff of KVPY 2016 SA would be?",
  "response": "The cutoff marks for the Kishore Vaigyanik Protsahan Yojana (KVPY) can vary every year based on various factors such as the difficulty level of the exam, number of candidates appearing, and overall performance. For the KVPY SA stream in 2016, the cutoff marks were:\n\n- For General Category: 55 marks out of 100\n- For SC/ST Category: 45 marks out of 100\n- For PwD Category: 45 marks out of 100\n\nThese cutoff scores are essentially the minimum marks required to be eligible for the interview stage. However, they can vary slightly each year. Always refer to the official KVPY website or reliable sources for the most accurate and updated information.",
